comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:14.472Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm search 'validate placeholder metadata blocked_reason unblock_note repro_steps' --limit 20; pm search 'External audit follow-up: validation and large-output ergonomics' --limit 20; pm list-open --limit 20. Net-new because existing validation items focus on structural checks,not semantic low-signal metadata detection."
  "2026-04-05T03:08:05.985Z",codex-agent,"Scope extension for external issue #4: add default-on remediation command templates for missing resolution metadata in pm validate output details."
  "2026-04-05T03:26:56.486Z",codex-agent,"Progress: added default-on resolution remediation hints in validate output details. Resolution check now emits deterministic pm update <id> command templates for missing resolution/expected_result/actual_result fields (additive detail fields only, warning tokens unchanged), so both TOON and JSON outputs include actionable remediation by default. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts passed."
  "2026-04-05T03:46:59.542Z",codex-agent,Added default remediation command templates for missing resolution fields in validate outputs; smoke checked validate --check-resolution --json emits missing_resolution_remediation_hints with pm update templates.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:14.472Z",codex-agent,Checks should be configurable and avoid false positives by supporting per-rule opt-outs and rule versioning.
